President Barack Obama will be awarding Dakota Meyer, a former Marine Corps Corporal, the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions in Afghanistan in 2009. Meyer will be the third living recipient, and the first Marine, to receive the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He enlisted in the Marine Corps in 2006 and served in both Iraq and Afghanistan. Meyer's military decorations include the Purple Heart Medal, Navy and Marine Corps Commendation Medal with "V" device for valor, and the Combat Action Ribbon, among others. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who display gallantry and intrepidity above and beyond the call of duty, involving great personal bravery or self-sacrifice.